          <msContents>
            <summary>Supplementary text to the well-known Bhagavadgītā, expanding on the rich philosophical and cosmological discourse between the legendary prince Arjuna and the legendary king Kṛṣṇa, understood as an avatāra of the deity Viṣṇu. Presented as a conversation between Arjuna and Kṛṣṇa.</summary>
            <textLang mainLang="san">In Sanskrit</textLang>
            <msItem>
              <title>Uttaragītā</title>
              <title type="vernacular">उत्तरगीता</title>
              <colophon>Colophon: iti hariḥ om̐ tatsadīti śrīmanmahābhārate śatasahasikāyāṃ vayyaśikyā aśvamedhaparvaṇīsūpaniṣatsūbrahmavidyāyāṃ śrīkṛṣṇārjunasaṃvāde uttaragītāyāṃ tṛtīyodhyāyaḥ // 3 // śrīrāmāyanamaḥ // śrīkṛṣṇāyanamaḥ // śrīkāśīviśvesvarāyanamaḥ // (f. 19r)</colophon>
            </msItem>
          </msContents>
